    "updated_at": "2012-02-06T20:59:17Z",
    "body": "I'm hoping that the final copy of the arguments out of the shim struct and into the arguments of the rust function will be eliminated through inlining. I'm not sure if that's what you are referring to though.\n\nI believe that our C calls currently copy the arguments into a struct on the Rust stack then copy that struct to the C stack.\n",
