    "body": "@pcwalton Rust->C do not currently write directly into the C stack because that is specific to i386.  I wanted to avoid having to write code that was specific to a particular calling convention, even at the price of some performance, in order to get 64-bit working.  (I think such optimizations might make sense now, though---particularly as #1402 points out that LLVM doesn't really handle the calling conventions completely _anyway_)\n",
    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
