    "body": "The arg struct is not copied, but the shim function will load values out of it and re-push them onto the new stack.  The old code used to literally write the argument values directly into the target stack.  This made sense on i386 but on x86_64 it's much more complex to figure out which values will go on the stack etc.\n",
    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
