    "created_at": "2012-02-14T08:17:18Z",
    "updated_at": "2012-02-14T08:17:39Z",
    "body": "I guess we can change rust_task to ignore kill requests once tasks have reentered the rust stack. For tasks implementing event loops they can peek at some monitor port looking for a message indicating that the runtime is failing and figure out how to terminate gracefully.\n",
    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
