    "created_at": "2012-02-14T15:09:16Z",
    "updated_at": "2012-02-14T15:09:16Z",
    "body": "So when a top-level task fails, it propagates errors to its children?  I guess I don't understand our error propagation model, I thought it went from the leaves up.  It seems like code running on C stacks ought to be able to run in an unsupervised task or something like that.\n",
