    "created_at": "2016-07-14T19:53:31Z",
    "updated_at": "2016-07-14T19:53:31Z",
    "body": "Please forgive this resurrection, but this issue is linked from a y-combinator piece and a few other sites, and I recently had a noob ask about it, so I'm noting that, per this issue & later changes, calling Rust from C is [simple](https://doc.rust-lang.org/book/ffi.html#calling-rust-code-from-c):\n\n``` rust\n#[no_mangle]\npub extern fn hello_rust() -> *const u8 {\n    \"Hello, world!\\0\".as_ptr()\n}\n```\n\n``` C\n#include \"stdio.h\"\nconst char *hello_rust(void);\nint main(void) {\n    printf(\"%.32s\\n\", hello_rust());\n}\n```\n",
